additional_house_rules:
- No smoking please
- I ask that you please respect my property by not touching any of my books, clothes, or anything that hasn't been explicitly offered for your use. Thanks!
- The walls are thin so please keep the volume down after 9pm, especially on weekdays.
- Do not forget the keys at home as you will get locked out of the main door downstairs, and please lock the door when leaving or while at home.
description:
Come stay on a beautiful tree-lined street in Downtown Brooklyn Heights! My place is a cosy one bedroom very close to the Brooklyn Bridge Park, Dumbo galleries, cafes, restaurants, shopping centers, and every subway / bus line you will need to get around.

The apartment is on the 5th floor of a walkup which means four flights of stairs. It has a separate kitchen, huge windows, lots of natural light, and even a balcony. 

 A perfect spot for couples and business travelers!

Warm, sunny, eclectically decorated 1 bedroom in a quirky old building. The photos speak for themselves !

The entire apartment.

I respect whatever space or interaction my guests need! I recognize that sometimes it's nice to get to know your host, but many others prefer minimal interaction. I follow your lead and am always there to ensure a great stay, answer questions, or anything you require.

State st is a very quiet, residential street that's a mixture of cultures and ages. Just one block down however is bustling Court t where you can find unlimited options of food, banks, pharmacies, grocery and wine stores, cafes, gyms, shopping, laundry, pretty much anything you need within minutes of the apartment.

Within 10 minutes from my place, you will have access to the 2, 3, 4, 5, R, F, G, A, C subway lines, as well as a ton of busses. It's a very central area and exceptionally convenient as far as public transportation !

Note; it's an old building, which comes with lots of charm, but here are a few details you should know: 

- the shower takes a few minutes to run hot 
- it's a 5 story walk-up (a good daily workout, but not for someone who has trouble with stairs.)
- it is New York City; please help keep it pest free by never leaving dishes or food or garbage out!

hosts.about:
I'm a Lebanese artist living in Brooklyn! I love to eat, drink and go dancing. Meeting new people and visiting places I've never been is basically what I live for, along with spending time in my studio making objects. I speak English, Arabic and French, and make amazing hummos. 

Check out my art work here: (URL HIDDEN) or my instagram: @laranasserous

xxx
